owing any additional mobs to spawn.  I ran into this in Fort Ghelsba, where a Mithra had trained every single Orc in all of Fort Ghelsba, up near Warchief, and was training her shield skill.  A couple of my LS friends were trying to level, and she threatened MPK if they touched any of &quot;her orcs.&quot;  I promptly switched to WHM, and headed over.  I /t'd her and said by keeping all these mobs up here alive, you're robbing these people of any chance to gain experience.  She just kept on complaining, so Banishga II, Elemental Seal Waterga, Stonega, Banishga II took care of everything.  <br><br>Pretty much, I'm just trying to say that we need to be courteous to others when we're farming our mobs.  It's fine normally, go to a corner of the zone where not too many people are, and for God's sake, if you're training Yags, and a Lv. 12 takes ONE off of your train, simply because it's Decent Challenge, and he needs experience, don't berate him for it.  I'm sure you can live with one less Yagudo.  And how do you avoid this?  Kill off your train, and start over, or simply kill one by one.  Thank you for your time.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />~Simplicity~ [Remora]<br>WHM58/BLM29<br>Cooking: 22.3 &gt;.&gt;<br>Fishing:&nbsp;&nbsp;7.2 m(_ _)m</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
