n exp from it.<br><br>Those are strictly defined &quot;rules&quot; (mechanism) that have been designed for the game and everyone of us has to agree unless we can force/ask the game designers to change it. But there is a moral factor that is not counted in those. A lv50 killing Lizzards in Valkurm Dunes for fun/skill up knowing fully well that there are lv12~14 parties trying to earn exp on those because they don't know anything else to kill is morally wrong. The lv50 has a many options on what to skill up on (ie. many other zones that are not occupied by exp parties) while the exp party has very limited choices. A player trying to 'steal' a mob that has become unclaimed (due to charm/attacking a train...etc) knowing fully well that the other player have been fighting/claiming it for a while is also morally wrong.<br><br>So I think in this case: <br>-Tryst is (morally) wrong for trying to claim/attack the train made by Willow knowing fully well that a portion of it is originally claimed (or attacked) by Willow. The very fact that you trying to re-claim the mobs that have been accidentally attacked by Willow is a good enough reason.<br><br>-Willow is wrong (not about moral) claiming that the whole train is his when it is not due to the game mechanism that you can't claim more than 1 mob for long.<br><br>-The mithra in the Outpost is wrong (by the rules of the game agreed upon playing) because she threatens someone (harassment) and attempting to MPK (even though she haven't commited it). She is also wrong (same reason as Willow) for claiming monsters that she's not claiming (technically).<br><br>-Chakrila is being rude for slapping someone who don't know well and/or he doesn't know you. You are morally wrong for skilling up on the lizards knowing fully well that there are exp parties near by trying to gain exp on them. You do have the option to skill up in another area (such as Buburimu, Jugner or Passhow.. etc) and you choose not to do so. You're also morally wrong for telling a lie that you '/poke' Tryst but you actually '/slap' him. Whether it is a large or small telling a lie like that makes you look like a scamer (even if you aren't), is that right?<br><br><i><span class="sm">Edited, Thu Mar 17 13:38:20 2005 by kenki</span class="sm"></i></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?8953" target="akztarg">http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?8953</a><br>War 65, Mnk 60, Rng 55, Brd 40, Bst 37, Whm 40, Nin 33, Thf 36... Drk (x) Smn (x) - Use Chaosbringer to hunt for C.Ruby, good idea (?)</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
